ZH: 请把话筒递给我。
EN: Please pass me the microphone.

ZH: 他拿着话筒在台上演讲。
EN: He held the microphone to speak on stage.

ZH: 我的话筒坏了，我需要修理。
EN: My microphone is broken, I need to get it fixed.

ZH: 这个话筒是新买的。
EN: This microphone is newly bought.

ZH: 大家都在等待着我使用话筒。
EN: Everyone is waiting for me to use the microphone.

ZH: 话筒的声音很清晰。
EN: The microphone's sound is very clear.

ZH: 学会使用话筒对于演讲很重要。
EN: It's important to learn how to use a microphone for public speaking.

ZH: 我从未用过这么复杂的话筒。
EN: I have never used such a complex microphone before.

ZH: 请把话筒插到音响上。
EN: Please plug the microphone into the speaker.

ZH: 这款话筒的音质非常好。
EN: The sound quality of this microphone is very good.

ZH: 记得把话筒开关打开。
EN: Remember to turn on the microphone switch.

ZH: 他有一个特别喜欢的话筒品牌。
EN: He has a favorite brand of microphone.

ZH: 话筒的线有点松动。
EN: The microphone's wire is a bit loose.

ZH: 别忘记在会议上用话筒。
EN: Don't forget to use the microphone at the meeting.

ZH: 他把话筒放在台上。
EN: He placed the microphone on the stage.

ZH: 这个话筒的音响效果很出色。
EN: This microphone has an excellent sound effect.

ZH: 我想试一下用话筒唱歌。
EN: I want to try singing with a microphone.

ZH: 把话筒放到你嘴边，声音更清晰。
EN: Put the microphone near your mouth, the sound will be clearer.

ZH: 话筒上的按钮是用来调节音量的。
EN: The buttons on the microphone are used to adjust the volume.

ZH: 在会议上用话筒让大家更容易听到。
EN: Using a microphone at the meeting makes it easier for everyone to hear.
